DURBAN - As the Easter weekend draws to an end, thousands of travellers are facing frustration on the roads. Traffic along the N3 from Durban towards Johannesburg was massively delayed following protests along the highway on Monday morning. By afternoon, the road had been re-opened, but travellers were facing massive delays. READ: Cele rushes to Mooi River following protest Other major roads across the country were also experiencing heavy traffic on Monday afternoon. Authorities said there's a massive backlog and urged motorists to be patient. Officials earlier urged holidaymakers travelling from Durban to delay their journeys. READ: Authorities on high alert as holidaymakers return home The route between KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng is one of the busiest during the Easter long weekend. Images of trucks being set alight did the rounds on Monday morning eNCA